p in the familial process: from the difficulties of romantic relationships, to decision-making dilemmas at conception, to the often celebratory moment of birth, and finally to the hardships that accompany the early years of the child's life, and beyond.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 20. Jun 2019) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Gender Studies.2bisacsh1 aNelson, Timothy J., eauthor.40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520955134423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520955134.jpg  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aEBA_FAO